      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(voice-call): avoid OpenAI realtime double greeting",
        "body": "Fixes #85846\n\n## Summary\n- Avoid the voice-call plugin's duplicate OpenAI realtime greeting by not calling `triggerGreeting()` for OpenAI when server VAD will auto-create the first response.\n- Preserve the configured outbound initial message for OpenAI by passing the built greeting instructions into the OpenAI realtime session instructions.\n- Keep explicit `triggerGreeting()` initial greetings enabled for non-OpenAI realtime providers such as Google.\n- Add focused realtime handler regressions for no-message, OpenAI initial-message, and non-OpenAI initial-message paths.\n\n## Why\nOpenAI realtime server VAD defaults to `create_response: true`. For outbound voice calls with an initial message, the telephony handler also queued an explicit greeting via `triggerGreeting()`, so OpenAI could create two back-to-back responses on the first caller turn. The repair now gives OpenAI the initial message once through session instructions and leaves the explicit greeting trigger disabled for that provider.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 20 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts`\n\nNote: commit is SSH-signed locally and verified with `git log --show-signature -1` after rebasing onto current `main`. No live Twilio/OpenAI call was run in this environment.",
        "branch": "fix-85846-openai-realtime-double-greeting",
